data.description: Check out this amazing log house on nearly 10 acres of land in Williamston, South Carolina. The great room has high cathedral ceilings, wood burning stove and lots of windows that let in natural light. The kitchen comes with all the necessary appliances. The dining room has wooden french doors that lead to a screened porch with a wood burning fireplace. On this porch, there's a access to a large deck, perfect for parties, checking out the wildlife or relaxing with a cup of coffee. On the main floor, you'll find the master suite with a walk-in closet. Upstairs, there are two big bedrooms with plenty of storage space and full a bath. The property offers stunning views and even has a creek running through it. There's a spot for an RV with an electrical hookup. The shop offers two office spaces with their own heating and cooling systems along with a system in place for heated floors throughout the shop. The car lift does not convey. The shop is ideal for businesses, hobbies, or anything else you can think of.
